The Daily Signal spoke to him about the issues confronting America’s veterans and his leadership of the Department of Veterans Affairs.
Rob Bluey: Tell us about the mission of Veterans Affairs and what your priorities are as secretary for the department.
I’m sitting underneath the quote from the father of what was first the Veterans Bureau and now Veterans Affairs.
We take care of about nine and a half million of America’s veterans.
So choice is the key for our veterans, both on the medical front and on the education front.